HEADWORD: Tamworth
<hw>Tam"worth</hw> <pr>(t⟦acr⟧m"w⟦ucr⟧rth)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From <etsep>Tamworth</etsep>, Staffordshire, England.]</ety>
<def>One of a long-established English breed of large pigs. They are
red, often spotted with black, with a long snout and erect or forwardly
pointed ears, and are valued as bacon producers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

